<i>[Till The End of the Moon]</i>

17
00:01:36,060 --> 00:01:38,580
<i>[Episode 23]</i>

18
00:01:52,150 --> 00:01:53,820
Ye Qingyu.

19
00:01:57,850 --> 00:01:59,410
You're awake.

20
00:01:59,410 --> 00:02:01,550
You were drunk last night.

21
00:02:01,550 --> 00:02:03,360
Do you have a headache?

22
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:09,080
I was being impulsive after drinking last night.

23
00:02:09,810 --> 00:02:14,010
Please don't take it to heart.

24
00:02:18,650 --> 00:02:21,210
I can tell what's real and what's not.

25
00:02:21,860 --> 00:02:23,640
That's good, then.

26
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:32,890
Ye Qingyu, I…

27
00:02:32,890 --> 00:02:35,450
You're here to ask me about the antidote, right?

28
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:42,360
You can be frank with me.

29
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:46,760
I can't stay here any longer.

30
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:48,200
Give me the antidote.

31
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:50,500
And I'll leave the capital by myself.

32
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:56,020
Why? Is it because of me?

33
00:03:03,610 --> 00:03:08,010
I really don't know if I should feel honored

34
00:03:08,010 --> 00:03:09,170
or unfortunate.

35
00:03:09,170 --> 00:03:12,980
Ye Qingyu, it's impossible between us.

36
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:17,450
What do I have to do for you to give me the antidote?

37
00:03:17,450 --> 00:03:19,040
There is no antidote.

38
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,390
What?

39
00:03:26,050 --> 00:03:30,720
His Majesty told me that the pill he forced you to swallow

40
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:33,500
was just a regular tonic pill.

41
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,930
Tantai Jin!

42
00:03:37,930 --> 00:03:40,960
So, you're free.

43
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:46,150
Tantai Jin said he gave the antidote to you.

44
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:48,680
I can never leave your side

45
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:51,050
as long as you use that excuse to keep me around.

46
00:03:52,490 --> 00:03:54,570
Why did you tell me the truth?

47
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:56,020
You're a woman of your word.

48
00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:57,910
And I enjoyed momentary pleasure with you.

49
00:03:57,910 --> 00:04:01,790
I dare not expect God to favor me again.

50
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:09,130
Pianran, encountering you

51
00:04:09,130 --> 00:04:12,630
was the most fortunate event that has happened to me.

52
00:04:21,850 --> 00:04:23,610
What if I...

53
00:04:23,610 --> 00:04:26,360
feel like staying in the capital again?

54
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:31,440
It's okay. You can go wherever you want.

55
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:32,810
If you don't wish to see me,

56
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:36,360
I can write to His Majesty and leave the capital myself.

57
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:40,630
Ye Qingyu, are you truly a fool?

58
00:04:40,630 --> 00:04:42,740
Or are you pretending to be one?

59
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:48,970
Forget it. I can't bother to explain it to you.

60
00:04:48,970 --> 00:04:52,560
Anyway, I'm free now.

61
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:54,560
I can go wherever I want.

62
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:57,650
Now, I feel like staying in the capital again.

63
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:00,070
Pianran.

64
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:07,430
So, we can spend time with each other again.

65
00:05:07,430 --> 00:05:09,140
Right?

66
00:05:09,140 --> 00:05:11,190
I guess.

67
00:05:11,190 --> 00:05:13,310
It depends on your performance.

68
00:05:38,850 --> 00:05:42,950
Xiwu, have you two reconciled with each other?

69
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:45,320
There's nothing to reconcile about.

70
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:47,990
There are no overnight grudges between husband and wife.

71
00:05:47,990 --> 00:05:51,630
Little One, you must tell me if you feel troubled.

72
00:05:51,630 --> 00:05:54,350
Don't hold it in and suffer alone.

73
00:05:54,350 --> 00:05:55,580
I'm perfectly fine.

74
00:05:55,580 --> 00:05:56,960
How can that be?

75
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:59,220
Tantai Jin is the emperor now.

76
00:05:59,220 --> 00:06:01,320
And our family has fallen from grace.

77
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:06,580
You may inevitably be subjected to humiliation in front of him.

78
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:08,430
What humiliation?

79
00:06:08,430 --> 00:06:12,550
I made him sleep on the floor last night.

80
00:06:12,550 --> 00:06:16,630
Second Sister, you're excellent at taming your husband.

81
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:21,950
Speaking of which, Bingchang hasn't returned home yet

82
00:06:21,950 --> 00:06:24,740
since she arrived in the capital.

83
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:28,300
Now, Eldest Sister is the noble Madam Xuancheng.

84
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:31,280
Tantai Jin lets her live in the palace.

85
00:06:32,190 --> 00:06:35,360
I think he's afraid that Xiao Lin may snatch her away.

86
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:37,630
It's always safer to hide in the palace.

87
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:38,950
When she's in the Palace of Jing,

88
00:06:38,950 --> 00:06:40,370
Xiao Lin will have to hold back.

89
00:06:40,370 --> 00:06:41,970
They won't ignore her.

90
00:06:41,970 --> 00:06:46,120
Has Bingchang suffered any grievances then?

91
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:47,360
Don't worry, Grandmother.

92
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,440
Tantai Jin isn't that kind of person.

93
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:50,560
If you're still worried,

94
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,630
I'll visit Eldest Sister after dinner

95
00:06:52,630 --> 00:06:55,600
and ask her if she's willing to move back.

96
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,980
Good.

97
00:06:57,980 --> 00:07:00,530
Come on, eat up.

98
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,540
That's the gist of it.

99
00:07:05,540 --> 00:07:08,270
Sister, you must have suffered for the past few days.

100
00:07:08,270 --> 00:07:11,030
I'll apologize to you on Tantai Jin's behalf.

101
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:12,860
There's no need to say that, Sister.

102
00:07:12,860 --> 00:07:16,360
How could I make the emperor apologize to me?

103
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:20,260
I'm happy for you that you two have reconciled with each other.

104
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:23,500
That's typical of Tantai Jin. He's so capricious.

105
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,730
Just don't take it to heart.

106
00:07:25,730 --> 00:07:28,320
If you can't get used to living in the palace,

107
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:31,130
I can speak with Tantai Jin and tell him to let you leave.

108
00:07:31,130 --> 00:07:33,690
You can go home and live with Grandmother and Father.

109
00:07:33,690 --> 00:07:35,290
No need.

110
00:07:38,370 --> 00:07:40,830
I mean, His Majesty must have his reasons to let me stay in the palace.

111
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:44,650
Besides, I've already gotten used to it.

112
00:07:44,650 --> 00:07:47,720
I shouldn't go home and disturb Grandmother and Father.

113
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,540
But…

114
00:07:48,540 --> 00:07:51,380
Second Sister, we are both married women.

115
00:07:51,380 --> 00:07:53,760
How can we keep living in our parents' home?

116
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:56,730
It's good for you that you can stay by His Majesty's side.

117
00:07:56,730 --> 00:07:58,330
But me?

118
00:07:58,330 --> 00:08:01,280
Sixth Prince is still missing.

119
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:05,780
If I live at home, I'll look like a divorced woman instead.

120
00:08:05,780 --> 00:08:08,970
Our neighbors will criticize us.

121
00:08:08,970 --> 00:08:12,620
It's better if I live in the palace.

122
00:08:14,530 --> 00:08:15,540
All right.

123
00:08:15,540 --> 00:08:18,100
But Grandmother and Father do miss you very much.

124
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:20,050
Please visit them when you're free.

125
00:08:20,050 --> 00:08:23,140
All right. Thanks for your concern.

126
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:26,220
Then I'll head back first.

127
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:39,700
<i>Tantai Jin still loves her deeply despite how Second Sister treated him.</i>

128
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:42,940
<i>If I stay in the palace, I might still have a chance.</i>

129
00:08:42,940 --> 00:08:48,640
<i>If I move home, it'll be difficult to see Tantai Jin again.</i>

130
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:52,080
<i>I didn't expect that he had no desire for me.</i>

131
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:54,720
<i>If I want to live off him,</i>

132
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:57,960
<i>I must be of use to him.</i>

133
00:09:19,050 --> 00:09:20,770
Your Majesty.

134
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:26,910
You may speak from there.

135
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:31,810
I...

136
00:09:31,810 --> 00:09:33,670
I don't know what I have done wrong

137
00:09:33,670 --> 00:09:35,910
to make you dislike me.

138
00:09:35,910 --> 00:09:37,590
You have done nothing wrong.

139
00:09:37,590 --> 00:09:39,460
Once I capture Xiao Lin,

140
00:09:39,460 --> 00:09:42,800
I'll let you two reunite.

141
00:09:45,270 --> 00:09:49,260
Your Majesty, do you have to capture Prince Xuancheng?

142
00:09:53,580 --> 00:09:58,000
Why did you think I allowed you to stay here in the first place?

143
00:10:01,390 --> 00:10:07,000
Your Majesty, I have something to discuss with you.

144
00:10:21,420 --> 00:10:24,170
The rations I borrowed two days ago will run out in another two days.

145
00:10:24,170 --> 00:10:25,610
We're out of medicine and bandages, too.

146
00:10:25,610 --> 00:10:26,440
What should we do?

147
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:28,480
Is there any nearby county which we haven't borrowed rations from?

148
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,670
There's none.

149
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:31,020
Try again then.

150
00:10:31,020 --> 00:10:34,070
Your Highness, you're now a rebel.

151
00:10:34,070 --> 00:10:36,100
We're all wanted criminals.

152
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:37,850
Forget about borrowing rations.

153
00:10:37,850 --> 00:10:42,640
They have already done us one last favor by not reporting us to the local authorities.

154
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:45,470
Junior Martial Uncle, what are our odds of winning

155
00:10:45,470 --> 00:10:47,470
if we keep this up?

156
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:51,630
Well, you see…

157
00:10:51,630 --> 00:10:53,950
We have no chance of winning. Right?

158
00:10:53,950 --> 00:10:56,010
There's nothing we can do about it.

159
00:10:56,010 --> 00:10:57,970
Do you still remember you, me, and Qingyu

160
00:10:57,970 --> 00:10:59,800
used to discuss state affairs in the capital?

161
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:02,640
<i>Common folks always suffer</i>

162
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:04,820
<i>no matter how the kingdom does.</i>

163
00:11:04,820 --> 00:11:07,580
<i>It's always been like this.</i>

164
00:11:07,580 --> 00:11:10,020
<i>I've engaged the people of Jing in battle on numerous occasions.</i>

165
00:11:10,020 --> 00:11:11,520
<i>Although Jing Kingdom is our enemy,</i>

166
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:13,690
<i>their soldiers and civilians</i>

167
00:11:13,690 --> 00:11:15,600
<i>are made of flesh and blood too.</i>

168
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,750
Qingyu was right.

169
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:21,380
To common folks, war is detrimental no matter if it's won or lost.

170
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:23,450
Now, Tantai Jin fights for peace.

171
00:11:23,450 --> 00:11:27,020
People want him to unite the world.

172
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:31,630
Maybe I should lead our remaining people southward

173
00:11:31,630 --> 00:11:33,650
and leave this place.

174
00:11:33,650 --> 00:11:34,630
How could you harbor such thoughts?

175
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:36,200
Your Highness!

176
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:40,710
Your Highness, the spy we planted in the Capital of Jing sent us a secret letter.

177
00:11:40,710 --> 00:11:42,550
It's for you.

178
00:11:45,420 --> 00:11:47,340
It's Bingchang's handwriting.

179
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:51,210
No wonder Tantai Jin allowed her to write to you.

180
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:53,160
The content of the letter praises his benevolence.

181
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:56,520
Looks like Tantai Jin is still bent on making you surrender.

182
00:11:56,520 --> 00:12:00,150
<i>[Tantai Jin rules the world with dignity and love. Everyone reveres him and he is diligent with politics. He is brilliant and divine and loves civilians as if they were his children.]</i>

183
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,460
Something's not right.

184
00:12:03,460 --> 00:12:04,980
What do you mean?

185
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:14,500
<i>[Help]</i>

186
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:24,000
<i>[Jingyao Gate]</i>

187
00:12:26,050 --> 00:12:27,810
Court dismissed.

188
00:12:31,240 --> 00:12:32,920
General Ye.

189
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,040
Your Majesty.

190
00:12:37,020 --> 00:12:40,000
Disaster relief impacts many people.

191
00:12:42,530 --> 00:12:44,040
You're from the Sheng Kingdom.

192
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:46,790
I feel most reassured to let you

193
00:12:46,790 --> 00:12:49,600
help the refugees to settle down.

194
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:51,720
I shall not fail you, Your Majesty.

195
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:53,140
Now, the world is united.

196
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:57,470
I desire for the people of Sheng Kingdom to settle down and recoup their losses

197
00:12:57,470 --> 00:12:59,880
more than anyone else.

198
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:03,830
And I appreciate your kindness more than anyone else.

199
00:13:05,770 --> 00:13:07,250
Today's the Qixi Festival.
<i>(Chinese festival similar to Valentine's Day)</i>

200
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:11,190
I heard that the night of Qixi in the Capital of Jing is the liveliest.

201
00:13:11,190 --> 00:13:12,830
Why don't you...

202
00:13:14,810 --> 00:13:18,360
leave the palace and go for a stroll with Pianran?

203
00:13:23,860 --> 00:13:25,830
Go ahead.

204
00:13:34,390 --> 00:13:36,360
<i>Ye Xiwu.</i>

205
00:13:44,170 --> 00:13:47,740
<i>Bravo!</i>

206
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:06,690
Let's go.

207
00:14:10,550 --> 00:14:13,550
Now, Sheng and Jing are united. The state is in peace.

208
00:14:13,550 --> 00:14:15,860
We can finally have a proper festival.

209
00:14:15,860 --> 00:14:18,000
That's right.

210
00:14:24,930 --> 00:14:27,220
You accomplished a good deed.

211
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:35,260
I just did what a ruler should do.

212
00:14:45,830 --> 00:14:47,140
Are you all right?

213
00:14:47,140 --> 00:14:48,890
I'm fine.

214
00:14:56,860 --> 00:14:58,450
It's crowded here.

215
00:14:58,450 --> 00:15:00,360
Today's the last day of the Water Festival.

216
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:01,810
And it's also the Qixi Festival.

217
00:15:01,810 --> 00:15:04,060
The townsfolk are all out on the streets.

218
00:15:04,060 --> 00:15:08,140
The liveliest day of the year is today.

219
00:15:10,770 --> 00:15:11,720
Tantai Jin,

220
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:14,220
why are they all wearing masks?

221
00:15:16,410 --> 00:15:18,390
It's for the seven-day-long deity parade during the Water Festival.

222
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:21,480
It is said that it will help exorcise demons and ghosts.

223
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:26,100
You'll understand if we run into one later.

224
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:27,340
<i>Masks for sale!</i>

225
00:15:28,930 --> 00:15:31,020
Sir, pick one.

226
00:15:32,530 --> 00:15:34,860
Let's get one and follow the customs.

227
00:15:34,860 --> 00:15:36,170
Okay.

228
00:15:36,170 --> 00:15:38,980
Don't just agree verbally. Pay up.

229
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:51,370
Come. This one suits you.

230
00:15:51,370 --> 00:15:53,070
I want this one.

231
00:15:58,370 --> 00:16:00,640
Okay, thank you.

232
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:02,130
Thank you.

233
00:16:02,130 --> 00:16:03,860
Let's go.

234
00:16:04,620 --> 00:16:07,470
Masks for sale!

235
00:16:07,470 --> 00:16:09,380
Masks for sale!

236
00:16:09,380 --> 00:16:12,170
Sir, take a look.

237
00:16:25,690 --> 00:16:28,250
I didn't expect that we would be able to enter the Capital of Jing so fast.

238
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:30,660
Keep your guard up. Stay cautious.

239
00:16:30,660 --> 00:16:32,380
This is enemy territory after all.

240
00:16:32,380 --> 00:16:33,030
Yes, sir.

241
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:33,900
All right.

242
00:16:33,900 --> 00:16:35,410
Let's go.

243
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:45,410
You scared me.

244
00:16:46,260 --> 00:16:47,890
Please feel free to try.

245
00:16:47,890 --> 00:16:49,640
Try this one. It's freshly made.

246
00:16:49,640 --> 00:16:51,980
- Thanks.
- Okay.

247
00:16:53,980 --> 00:16:55,820
- Does it taste good?
- Yes.

248
00:16:55,820 --> 00:16:56,770
Take a look at this.

249
00:16:56,770 --> 00:16:59,640
Exquisite craft for sale. It brings you good luck.

250
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:01,440
Take a look!

251
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:02,240
It's so pretty.

252
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:04,830
It's a white jade scepter.

253
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:11,020
<i>[Ward off evil and diseases]</i>

254
00:17:13,470 --> 00:17:15,260
Excuse me.

255
00:17:23,020 --> 00:17:25,620
<i>[Ward off evil and diseases]</i>

256
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:36,020
<i>[Ward off evil and diseases]</i>

257
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:47,770
<i>Bravo!</i>

258
00:17:54,080 --> 00:17:55,410
Like this.

259
00:18:06,770 --> 00:18:08,810
<i>Bravo!</i>

